column8:
i've been a widower for over 15 years and emotionally i've moved on.. i'm actually older than i list on my profile but discovered if i listed my real age most people won't look at my profile and usually people think i'm even younger than i'm listing there.. but ask me and i'll tell you..i'm 5'9 with reddish brown hair and brown eyes. i'm struggling to lose the weight i gained after my wife died and i'm about halfway to my goal.

i'm that mythical "nice guy." i really do get it.. if i tell you i'm going to call at 8, i call at 8.. if i'm 5 minutes late i apologize.. i go out of my way to help my friends. if you need something i can do i'll drop everything to do it for you. if you need to talk about it i'll listen. i understand that sometimes you just want to be held.. me too.

people also think i'm a good deal more conservative than i am.. you can't always tell a book by it's cover.. i have a definite naughty streak but i am polite and a little reserved. if i don't know someone i tend to err on the side of caution.

i find a lot of people remarking about how intelligent i look.. i'm not certain how they can tell but i pride myself on how much i know about things.. but even more i pride myself on how little i know and how much more there is to learn. if you're attracted to hot bodies i'm probably not your guy.. if you like cuddly teddy bears with hot brains.. then say hi!

i have a wide variety of interests. i am constantly learning and trying new things. i have some constants, i'm passionate about food, i love to cook and love learning about new cuisines and new ingredients. when i travel some place new i'm as happy wondering through a market as i am through a museum though i love museums too.

i enjoy nature and travel, have over a million frequent flyer miles accumulated and would love to find someone to share them with. i've traveled enough to realize how little i've seen... i've been on every continent but antarctica at least a couple of times... the list of places i want to go to will always be longer than the list of the places i've been...many years as a road warrior has made me long for a kindred spirit to travel with.

i'm happy to chat with most anyone. i've been meeting people from the net for a long time and i really prefer to keep things simple. i think if there is mutual interest meeting sooner rather than later is the only thing that makes sense. the longer you go without meeting the more your imagination fills in the gaps of the myriad of things it's impossible to tell online and while imagination tends to be perfect.. real people aren't.. i'm not a big believer in long distance romance so if you're across the country or on the other side of the world while i'm happy to chat i'm not apt to hop on a plane to come meet you.

i've pretty well come to the conclusion that dating sites don't work. you can tell so little about a person on line that the only thing that makes sense is when you meet people without expectations. dating sites by their very nature create expectations... i have no idea how the site comes up with the percentages of compatibility... just further reinforcement as cool and wonderful technology is 20 years of internet doesn't replace millions of years of human evolution. i really do give up... i think i have a much better chance at the lottery than i do of meeting someone interesting on this site... and i never buy tickets.. message me if you like but don't take offense if i don't reply...
column9:
i've stopped being a road warrior and gone back to teaching
college.. i love teaching.. life on the road consulting was
essentially teaching but i much prefer to be in the classroom..
column10:
cooking... i love to cook and entertain.. i'm constantly trying new things... i make my own jam i make pickles... cure meats make sausages.. smoke meat..

i love to figure out how to do something new..

i'm also really good at planning complicated travel itineraries. road trip with me? ;)
column11:
people constantly remark on how smart i look.. i'm not really sure
what smart looks like but i'm told that all the time.. other than
that i'm a natural red head so that's probably what most people
notice..
column12:
books... when i travel i tend to read mindless mysteries.. i love good travel narratives... i'm a big fan of paul theroux, bill bryson and peter mayle..

tv.. mostly downloads from the bbc.. science, nature, travel, cooking with the odd political satire or mystery thrown in for good measure..

food i love it all... cooking, dining out, wandering around markets.
column13:
something to read
good food
my passport
people to teach and learn from.. the more i teach the more i learn!
column14:
the futility of dating sites... they are so diametrically opposed
to how people meet in real life..generally women will give some
indication that they find you attractive in person, a smile, a
look, something.. which is impossible online, so we are reduced to
looking at pictures and words which no matter how photogenic and
articulate someone is.. it's far less information about attraction
than you'd have standing next to someone for 5 minutes.. the
profiles are odd... we can find out intimate details about how
someone thinks (assuming they answered questions honestly) but have
no idea if they'd find us interesting or attractive.. so guys are
reduced to messaging randomly and hoping... or sit and wait and
hope someone takes the initiative..
column15:
probably just hanging out by myself.. i'd love something a bit more
entertaining... make me and offer. ;)
column16: ask me and i'll probably tell you
column17:
you think people should meet from the net without expectations
like brainy guys that love to cook
